    {
      "kind": "content",
      "content": [
        {
          "anchor": "overview",
          "level": 2,
          "text": "Overview",
          "type": "heading"
        },
        {
          "type": "paragraph",
          "inlineContent": [
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": "In addition to any of the properties provided by the "
            },
            {
              "type": "reference",
              "isActive": true,
              "identifier": "doc://com.apple.documentation/documentation/glkit/glkbaseeffect"
            },
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": " class, your application must also configure the properties on the reflection map. The default value of the "
            },
            {
              "type": "reference",
              "isActive": true,
              "identifier": "doc://com.apple.documentation/documentation/glkit/glkbaseeffect/1488830-textureorder"
            },
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": " property provided by the base effect is modified to include the reflection map as a final texturing stage; your application can modify the value of that property to change the order in which texturing occurs."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "paragraph",
          "inlineContent": [
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": "The reflection map effect is calculated in accordance to section 2.11.4 of the OpenGL 2.1 specification "
            },
            {
              "type": "codeVoice",
              "code": "GL_REFLECTION_MAP"
            },
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": " glTexGen() mode. It requires a cube map texture to define the enclosing envelope from which to reflection map the scene."
            }
          ]
        }
      ]
    }
